tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a markedly elevated platelet distribution width, which may indicate increased platelet size variability, possibly due to platelet activation or turnover. No evidence of anemia, renal dysfunction, or electrolyte imbalance. Glycemic control is at the upper end of normal. Correlation with clinical context and possible follow-up of platelet indices is recommended.
